Test Branch 1.0.83390 Test 2026-04-29

Design

Crossbows now have +50% strength against melee, instead of +50% attack
AIs will no longer have child leaders, instead using the next adult in the succession or generating a new character if needed
All Hindu cities can now build Brahmins, without requiring Holy City/State Religion/Tolerance (Empires of the Indus)
Decreased Indian Unique Unit vision to be in line with other units, with the exception of Steppe Riders which retain extra vision (Empires of the Indus)
The owner of the unit, not the upgrading player, needs Polis to upgrade Steppe Riders (Empires of the Indus)
Mahapadma's unknown mother now has a name (Empires of the Indus)

UI

Added banded overlay effect for cities that will soon have a religion
Reworked event helptext for "subject not" - "Not Character is X" is now "Character is not X"
Added more detailed mission menu button info
Premade map selection with restricted nations is no longer saved, to prevent issues with leaders not appearing on Choose Leader screen

Bugs Fixed

Fixed double client initialization on network reconnection that could crash the host
Fixed tribes not capturing other tribes' settlements
Fixed improvements that spread religion not being highlighted when a religion is selected
Fix a rare Hall of Fame regeneration issue
Fixed some AI issues
Fixed missing opinion rate for marriage help when Tribal suitor marries heir
Fixed event portrait tooltip positioning
Fixed being able to push a an allied unit from its own territory
Fixed water control previews not updating with changes in vision
fixed some main menu Tech Tree issues
Fixed event helptext issue with Player/Leader/IndexSubjectNotAny
Fixed TRIBE_F, RELIGION_F, and TRAIT_F event text tags not working
Fixed some ambiguous map element name types
Fixed some Spanish text localization issues
Fixed map terrain not reverting correctly after closing timeline screen 
Fixed Modio & local maps not showing in mod browser
Fixed Modio upload not including mod version number (fixes incorrent update ! on install tab for local up-to-date mods)
Fixed null reference when clicking on maps in Mods Manage tab
Fixed leader customization panel breaking if characters exist with fixed portraits but no names (affects mods)
